Interface FrontBackCappedListInterface<T>

All Known Implementing Classes:
LinkedFrontBackCappedList
public interface FrontBackCappedListInterface<T>
An interface for a list. Entries in a list have positions that begin with 0. Entries can only be removed or added to the beginning (front) or end (back) of the list. Entries can be accessed from any position. The size of the list is limited ("capped"). When the limit is reached, no more entries can be added.
Author:
Jessica Masters

  • Method Details

    • addFront

      boolean addFront​(T newEntry)
      Adds a new entry to the beginning of the list if the list is not full. If the entry is added, entries currently in the list are shifted down and the list size is increased by 1.
      Parameters:
      newEntry - The object to be added as a new entry.
      Returns:
      true if the object was added, false if the list was full and thus the object was not added

    • addBack

      boolean addBack​(T newEntry)
      Adds a new entry to the end of the list if the list is not full. Entries currently in the list are unaffected. If the entry is added, the list size is increased by 1.
      Parameters:
      newEntry - The object to be added as a new entry.
      Returns:
      true if the object was added, false if the list was full and thus the object was not added

    • removeFront

      T removeFront()
      Removes an entry from the beginning of the list. Entries currently in the list are shifted up. If an entry is removed, the list size is decreased by 1.
      Returns:
      A reference to the removed entry or null if the list is empty.

    • removeBack

      T removeBack()
      Removes an entry from the end of the list. Entries currently in the list are unaffected. If an entry is removed, the list size is decreased by 1.
      Returns:
      A reference to the removed entry or null if the list is empty.

    • clear

      void clear()
      Removes all entries from this list.

    • getEntry

      T getEntry​(int givenPosition)
      Retrieves the entry at a given position in this list.
      Parameters:
      givenPosition - An integer that indicates the position of the desired entry.
      Returns:
      A reference to the indicated entry or null if the index is out of bounds.

    • indexOf

      int indexOf​(T anEntry)
      Determines the position in the list of a given entry. If the entry appears more than once, the first index is returned.
      Parameters:
      anEntry - the object to search for in the list.
      Returns:
      the first position the entry that was found or -1 if the object is not found.

    • lastIndexOf

      int lastIndexOf​(T anEntry)
      Determines the position in the list of a given entry. If the entry appears more than once, the last index is returned.
      Parameters:
      anEntry - the object to search for in the list.
      Returns:
      the last position the entry that was found or -1 if the object is not found.

    • contains

      boolean contains​(T anEntry)
      Determines whether an entry is in the list.
      Parameters:
      anEntry - the object to search for in the list.
      Returns:
      true if the list contains the entry, false otherwise

    • size

      int size()
      Gets the length of this list.
      Returns:
      The integer number of entries currently in the list.

    • isEmpty

      boolean isEmpty()
      Checks whether this list is empty.
      Returns:
      True if the list is empty, or false if the list contains one or more elements.

    • isFull

      boolean isFull()
      Checks whether this list is full.
      Returns:
      True if the list is full, or false otherwise.
